opsysCodeRev.name: opsysCodeRev
opsysCodeRev.description: A textual identification of network adapter's firmware revision level. For example: 7.15.1

opsysJobTimeout.name: opsysJobTimeout
opsysJobTimeout.description: The adapter job timeout period in seconds.

opsysCurrentJob.name: opsysCurrentJob
opsysCurrentJob.description: A textual description of the currently printing job containing the Source NOS, Source server, Source user, Job number, and Job size, separated by CR LF. A NULL string indicates no active job. For multiport adapters, this reflects job status of printer port 1.

opsysRAMSize.name: opsysRAMSize
opsysRAMSize.description: The size of the network adapter's RAM in bytes.

opsysNVRAMSize.name: opsysNVRAMSize
opsysNVRAMSize.description: The size of the network adapter's NVRAM in bytes.

opsysROMSize.name: opsysROMSize
opsysROMSize.description: The size of the network adapter's ROM in bytes.

opsysROMType.name: opsysROMType
opsysROMType.description: A textual description of the network adapter's ROM technology. Currently valid types are: MASK_ROM, OTP, FLASH, UV_EPROM, EEPROM, and OTHER.

opsysProtocols.name: opsysProtocols
opsysProtocols.description: A bitmap representing the protocols supported by the network adapter. Bit Value Protocol --- ----- ---------- 0 1 LexLink 1 2 Netware 2 4 AppleTalk 3 8 TCP/IP 4 16 reserved 5 32 reserved 6 64 NDS

opsysTimeToReset.name: opsysTimeToReset
opsysTimeToReset.description: The amount of time remaining until the adapter performs a power on reset. A value of -1 indicates no reset is scheduled. Setting to 0 causes the adapter to reset immediately. The only valid set value is 0.

opsysCardPartNo.name: opsysCardPartNo
opsysCardPartNo.description: A textual representation of the network adapter's part number.

opsysCardEC.name: opsysCardEC
opsysCardEC.description: A textual representation of the network adapter's EC level.

opsysCurrentJobTable.name: opsysCurrentJobTable
opsysCurrentJobTable.description: A table of current job information for each of the network adapter's printer ports.

opsysCurrentJobEntry.name: opsysCurrentJobEntry
opsysCurrentJobEntry.description: An entry containing job information for one printer port.

opsysCurrentJobEntryIndex.name: opsysCurrentJobEntryIndex
opsysCurrentJobEntryIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify job information for one printer port. Each entry corresponds to a value lexhdwrPortTableIndex.

opsysCurrentJobString.name: opsysCurrentJobString
opsysCurrentJobString.description: A textual description of the this printer port's currently printing job containing the Source NOS, Source server, Source user, Job number, and Job size, separated by CR LF. A NULL string indicates no active job.

opsysDeviceType.name: opsysDeviceType
opsysDeviceType.description: A two byte code representing the adapter's type.

opsysAdapterName.name: opsysAdapterName
opsysAdapterName.description: A Unicode representation of the adapter's name.

opsysAdapterCapabilities.name: opsysAdapterCapabilities
opsysAdapterCapabilities.description: A bitmap representing the capabilities of the adapter. Bit Value Frame type --- ---------- -------------------------- 31 0x80000000 NPANT via Netware and IP 30 0x40000000 Receive-only Fax 29 0x20000000 reserved 28 0x10000000 Adapter HTTP 27 0x08000000 Printer HTTP 26 0x04000000 HTTP Configuration Page 25 0x02000000 Copier Option

lexlinkActivated.name: lexlinkActivated
lexlinkActivated.description: The activation status of the LexLink protocol. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lexlinkNickname.name: lexlinkNickname
lexlinkNickname.description: The nickname assigned to the adapter for the LexLink protocol. Note that some adapters may not support the maximum length.

lexipxActivated.name: lexipxActivated
lexipxActivated.description: The activation status of the Netware protocol. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lexipxLoginName.name: lexipxLoginName
lexipxLoginName.description: The adapter's Netware login name. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lexipxNetNumber.name: lexipxNetNumber
lexipxNetNumber.description: The network number of the Netware network to which the adapter is connected.

lexipxSAPMode.name: lexipxSAPMode
lexipxSAPMode.description: The network adapter's current Netware SAP'ing status.

lexipxServerMode.name: lexipxServerMode
lexipxServerMode.description: The current Netware server mode of the adapter. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lexipxNumPorts.name: lexipxNumPorts
lexipxNumPorts.description: The number of Netware printer ports.

lexipxPortInfoTable.name: lexipxPortInfoTable
lexipxPortInfoTable.description: A table of Netware printer port information.

lexipxPortInfoEntry.name: lexipxPortInfoEntry
lexipxPortInfoEntry.description: An entry containing Netware printer port information.

lexipxPortInfoIndex.name: lexipxPortInfoIndex
lexipxPortInfoIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify Netware printer ports.

lexipxPortInfoPollIntvl.name: lexipxPortInfoPollIntvl
lexipxPortInfoPollIntvl.description: The Netware queue polling interval for this printer port.

lexipxPortInfoEnable.name: lexipxPortInfoEnable
lexipxPortInfoEnable.description: The Netware queue status of this printer port.

lexipxPortInfoBannerPage.name: lexipxPortInfoBannerPage
lexipxPortInfoBannerPage.description: The Netware queue banner page status for this printer port.

lexipxNumPrefServers.name: lexipxNumPrefServers
lexipxNumPrefServers.description: The maximum number of preferred Netware servers supported by this network adapter.

lexipxPrefSrvrTable.name: lexipxPrefSrvrTable
lexipxPrefSrvrTable.description: A table of the network adapter's preferred Netware servers.

lexipxPrefSrvrEntry.name: lexipxPrefSrvrEntry
lexipxPrefSrvrEntry.description: An entry containing preferred Netware server information.

lexipxPrefSrvrIndex.name: lexipxPrefSrvrIndex
lexipxPrefSrvrIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify preferred Netware servers.

lexipxPrefSrvrName.name: lexipxPrefSrvrName
lexipxPrefSrvrName.description: The name of this preferred Netware server. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lexipxConnSrvrTable.name: lexipxConnSrvrTable
lexipxConnSrvrTable.description: A table of connected Netware server information.

lexipxConnSrvrEntry.name: lexipxConnSrvrEntry
lexipxConnSrvrEntry.description: An entry containing connected Netware server information.

lexipxConnSrvrIndex.name: lexipxConnSrvrIndex
lexipxConnSrvrIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify connected Netware servers.

lexipxConnSrvrName.name: lexipxConnSrvrName
lexipxConnSrvrName.description: The name of this connected Netware server.

lexipxConnSrvrNet.name: lexipxConnSrvrNet
lexipxConnSrvrNet.description: The Netware network number of this connected Netware server.

lexipxConnSrvrNode.name: lexipxConnSrvrNode
lexipxConnSrvrNode.description: The Netware node address of the connected Netware server.

lexipxConnSrvrConnNum.name: lexipxConnSrvrConnNum
lexipxConnSrvrConnNum.description: The connection number of the connected Netware server (pserver mode only).

lexipxConnSrvrConnId.name: lexipxConnSrvrConnId
lexipxConnSrvrConnId.description: The connection ID of the connected Netware server (rprinter mode only).

lexipxConnSrvrPSConnID.name: lexipxConnSrvrPSConnID
lexipxConnSrvrPSConnID.description: The connection ID of the connected Netware pserver (rprinter mode only).

lexipxFrameType.name: lexipxFrameType
lexipxFrameType.description: A bitmap of the supported IPX frame types. Bit Value Frame type --- ----- -------------------------- 0 1 Token-Ring 1 2 Token-Ring Source Routed 2 4 Token-Ring SNAP 3 8 Token-Ring SNAP Source Routed 4 16 Ethernet 802.2 5 32 Ethernet 802.3 6 64 Ethernet Type 2 7 128 Ethernet SNAP

lexipxTrapTable.name: lexipxTrapTable
lexipxTrapTable.description: A table of IPX trap destination configurations.

lexipxTrapEntry.name: lexipxTrapEntry
lexipxTrapEntry.description: An entry containing an IPX trap destination's configuration.

lexipxTrapIndex.name: lexipxTrapIndex
lexipxTrapIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify IPX trap destinations.

lexipxTrapMask.name: lexipxTrapMask
lexipxTrapMask.description: The trap mask for the trap destination. It is implemented as a bitmap specifying a mask of intervention required conditions for which the adapter should send trap messages. Setting a bit to 1 enables the corresponding trap. A value of 511 will cause the adapter to send traps for all intervention required conditions. The bitmap is defined below: Bit Value Condition --- ----- -------------------------- 0 1 Output hopper full 1 2 Load Paper 2 4 Paper Jam 3 8 Toner Low 4 16 Service Required 5 32 Disk Error 6 64 Cover Opened 7 128 Page Complexity Error 8 256 Offline

lexipxTrapNetworkAddress.name: lexipxTrapNetworkAddress
lexipxTrapNetworkAddress.description: The IPX network address of the trap destination. (4 bytes)

lexipxTrapNodeAddress.name: lexipxTrapNodeAddress
lexipxTrapNodeAddress.description: The IPX node address of the trap destination. (6 bytes)

lexipxTrapType.name: lexipxTrapType
lexipxTrapType.description: The type of SNMP over IPX traps that will be sent by the adapter. Setting this variable to multiplexed(1) configures all intervention required conditions to send an irCondition trap (specific trap number 1) and for the clearing of intervention required conditions to send an irCleared trap (specific trap number 0). Setting this variable to individual(2) causes each intervention required condition to send its corresponding trap (specific traps numbered 2 through 10) and for the clearing of intervention required conditions to cause an irClearedTypeII trap (specific trap number 11). See the Trap Definitions Group for more information. Individual(2) is the default for IPX and is necessary for NMS annotations.

lexipxGSQ.name: lexipxGSQ
lexipxGSQ.description: The General Service Query (GSQ) interval. This is the period in seconds that the adapter waits after a failed GSQ before attempting another as it searches for Netware servers.

lextalkActivated.name: lextalkActivated
lextalkActivated.description: The activation status of the AppleTalk protocol. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lextalkAddress.name: lextalkAddress
lextalkAddress.description: The AppleTalk Address of the network card. This variable is not implemented on the XLe adapters.

lextalkName.name: lextalkName
lextalkName.description: The AppleTalk name of this adapter. This variable is not implemented on the XLe adapters.

lextalkZone.name: lextalkZone
lextalkZone.description: The AppleTalk zone name of this adapter. This variable is not implemented on the XLe adapters.

lextalkType.name: lextalkType
lextalkType.description: The AppleTalk type of this adapter. This variable is not implemented on the XLe adapters.

lextcpActivated.name: lextcpActivated
lextcpActivated.description: The activation status of the TCP/IP Protocol. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lextcpBootpEnable.name: lextcpBootpEnable
lextcpBootpEnable.description: The status of whether or not BOOTP is attempted to determine the IP parameters. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lextcpAddressServ.name: lextcpAddressServ
lextcpAddressServ.description: The IP address of the DHCP, BOOTP, or RARP server that provided the adapter's IP address.

lextcpNumNPAPservers.name: lextcpNumNPAPservers
lextcpNumNPAPservers.description: The maximum number of concurrent NPAP over TCP server connections.

lextcpNPAPserversTable.name: lextcpNPAPserversTable
lextcpNPAPserversTable.description: A table of NPAP over TCP server information.

lextcpNPAPserversEntry.name: lextcpNPAPserversEntry
lextcpNPAPserversEntry.description: An entry containing NPAP over TCP server information.

lextcpNPAPserverIndex.name: lextcpNPAPserverIndex
lextcpNPAPserverIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify NPAP over TCP servers.

lextcpNPAPserverAddress.name: lextcpNPAPserverAddress
lextcpNPAPserverAddress.description: The IP address of this NPAP over TCP server.

lexhttpEnable.name: lexhttpEnable
lexhttpEnable.description: The status of whether the adapter will enable the HTTP server. If this variable is changed, the adapter must be reset before the change will take effect. See opsysTimeToReset.

lexhttpNumLinks.name: lexhttpNumLinks
lexhttpNumLinks.description: The number of configurable HTTP links for the adapter.

lexhttpBytesRemaining.name: lexhttpBytesRemaining
lexhttpBytesRemaining.description: The number of bytes available to store HTTP link and label information.

lexhttpResetLinks.name: lexhttpResetLinks
lexhttpResetLinks.description: A control for restoring default values for HTTP link settings. Setting the variable to reset will cause all of the HTTP link settings to be reset to their default values.

lexhttpLinkTable.name: lexhttpLinkTable
lexhttpLinkTable.description: A table of HTTP Link settings.

lexhttpLinkTableEntry.name: lexhttpLinkTableEntry
lexhttpLinkTableEntry.description: An entry containing HTTP link settings.

lexhttpLinkTableIndex.name: lexhttpLinkTableIndex
lexhttpLinkTableIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify HTTP link settings.

lexhttpLinkTableStatus.name: lexhttpLinkTableStatus
lexhttpLinkTableStatus.description: The status of the HTTP link. Get operation: linkOff -- Server will not display the link personalOn -- Server will display the custom link useDefault -- Write-only defaultOff -- Reserved defaultOn -- Server will display the default link eraseCustom -- Write-only Set operation: linkOff -- Puts the link in linkOff status customOn -- Puts the link in customOn status useDefault -- Clears the Label and URL for this link and puts the . link in defaultOn status defaultOff -- Read-only defaultOn -- Read-only eraseCustom -- Clears the Label and URL for this link and puts the . link in linkOff status

lexhttpLinkTableLabel.name: lexhttpLinkTableLabel
lexhttpLinkTableLabel.description: The text to be displayed as the label of this HTTP link. It may be set to define a custom link. Note that when read, this always reflects what the server would display. As such, if the status of this link is defaultOn, it will not return your custom label if read even though it has been stored. Setting the status for this link to customOn will activate your custom link label. Remember that setting the status of this link to eraseCustom or useDefault clears this variable.

lexhttpLinkTableURL.name: lexhttpLinkTableURL
lexhttpLinkTableURL.description: The URL to be hyperlinked to by the HTTP link. It may be set to define a custom link. Note that when read, this always reflects what the server would use. As such, if the status of this link is defaultOn, it will not return your custom URL if read even though it has been stored. Setting the status for this link to customOn will activate your custom link URL. Remember that setting the status of this link to eraseCustom or useDefault clears this variable.

lexhttpConfigEnable.name: lexhttpConfigEnable
lexhttpConfigEnable.description: The status of whether HTTP configuration page is enabled.

lexdhcpDhcpEnable.name: lexdhcpDhcpEnable
lexdhcpDhcpEnable.description: The status of whether DHCP is enabled.

lexdhcpRarpEnable.name: lexdhcpRarpEnable
lexdhcpRarpEnable.description: The status of whether RARP is enabled.

lexdhcpAddressSource.name: lexdhcpAddressSource
lexdhcpAddressSource.description: The method by which the current IP parameters were obtained.

lexdhcpWinsStatus.name: lexdhcpWinsStatus
lexdhcpWinsStatus.description: The adapter's WINS server registration status.

lexdhcpWinsServer.name: lexdhcpWinsServer
lexdhcpWinsServer.description: The IP address of the WINS server.

lexdhcpLeaseLength.name: lexdhcpLeaseLength
lexdhcpLeaseLength.description: The length of the adapter's DHCP address lease in seconds.

lexdhcpTimetoExpire.name: lexdhcpTimetoExpire
lexdhcpTimetoExpire.description: The number of seconds until the DHCP address lease expires.

lexdhcpDNSServer.name: lexdhcpDNSServer
lexdhcpDNSServer.description: The IP address of the DNS server.

lexhdwrNumPorts.name: lexhdwrNumPorts
lexhdwrNumPorts.description: The number of printer ports supported by this network adapter.

lexhdwrPortTable.name: lexhdwrPortTable
lexhdwrPortTable.description: A table of the adapter's printer port hardware settings.

lexhdwrPortTableEntry.name: lexhdwrPortTableEntry
lexhdwrPortTableEntry.description: An entry containing printer port hardware settings.

lexhdwrPortTableIndex.name: lexhdwrPortTableIndex
lexhdwrPortTableIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify printer ports.

lexhdwrPortTableType.name: lexhdwrPortTableType
lexhdwrPortTableType.description: The type of attachment for this printer port.

lexhdwrPortTableParm1.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm1
lexhdwrPortTableParm1.description: For serial and parallel ports, this is the port timeout in seconds. For internal ports, this parameter is unused.

lexhdwrPortTableParm2.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm2
lexhdwrPortTableParm2.description: For serial ports, this is the baud rate in bits per second. For parallel ports, this is the port mode and is defined as follows: standard(0), enhanced(1) For internal ports, this parameter is unused.

lexhdwrPortTableParm3.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm3
lexhdwrPortTableParm3.description: For serial ports, this is the parity and is defined as follows: none(0), odd(1), even(2), space(3), mark(4) For parallel and internal ports, this parameter is unused.

lexhdwrPortTableParm4.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm4
lexhdwrPortTableParm4.description: For serial ports, this is the number of data bits. For parallel and internal ports, this parameter is unused.

lexhdwrPortTableParm5.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm5
lexhdwrPortTableParm5.description: For serial ports, this is the number of stop bits and is defined as follows: bitsOne(2), bitsOneAndHalf(3), bitsTwo(4) For parallel and internal ports, this parameter is unused.

lexhdwrPortTableParm6.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm6
lexhdwrPortTableParm6.description: For serial ports, this is the pacing mode and is defined as follows: paceDtr(0), paceXonXff(1) For non XLe parallel ports, this is the parallel protocol and is defined as follows: auto(2), ecp(3), byte(4), nibble(5), compatible(6) For internal ports, and XLe parallel ports this parameter is unused.

lexhdwrPortTableParm7.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm7
lexhdwrPortTableParm7.description: For all ports, this is the configured NPAP mode.

lexhdwrPortTableParm8.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm8
lexhdwrPortTableParm8.description: For all ports, this is the NPAP status.

lexhdwrPortTableParm9.name: lexhdwrPortTableParm9
lexhdwrPortTableParm9.description: For serial ports, this is the class of device attached. This variable is unused on the XLe adapters.

lexmacType.name: lexmacType
lexmacType.description: A textual representation of network medium to which the network adapter is attached (e.g. Ethernet).

lexmacSpeed.name: lexmacSpeed
lexmacSpeed.description: The speed, in bits per second, of the network medium to which the network adapter is attached.

lexmacConnType.name: lexmacConnType
lexmacConnType.description: The connection type by which the network adapter is connected to the network medium.

lexmacUAA.name: lexmacUAA
lexmacUAA.description: The network adapter's universally administered network address.

lexmacLAA.name: lexmacLAA
lexmacLAA.description: The network adapter's locally administered network address. A value of all zeros indicates that the LAA is not in use.

lextrapDestNum.name: lextrapDestNum
lextrapDestNum.description: The maximum number of IP trap destinations supported by this network adapter.

lextrapDestTable.name: lextrapDestTable
lextrapDestTable.description: A table of IP trap destination configurations.

lextrapDestEntry.name: lextrapDestEntry
lextrapDestEntry.description: An entry containing an IP trap destination configuration.

lextrapDestIndex.name: lextrapDestIndex
lextrapDestIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify IP trap destinations.

lextrapDestIPAddr.name: lextrapDestIPAddr
lextrapDestIPAddr.description: The IP address of the trap destination.

lextrapDestMask.name: lextrapDestMask
lextrapDestMask.description: The trap mask for the trap destination. It is implemented as a bitmap specifying a mask of intervention required conditions for which the adapter should send trap messages. Setting a bit to 1 enables the corresponding trap. A value of 1023 will cause the adapter to send traps for all intervention required conditions. The bitmap is defined below: Bit Value Condition --- ----- -------------------------- 0 1 Output hopper full 1 2 Load Paper 2 4 Paper Jam 3 8 Toner Low 4 16 Service Required 5 32 Disk Error 6 64 Cover Opened 7 128 Page Complexity Error 8 256 Offline 9 512 Printer MIB (RFC 1759)

lextrapIPTrapType.name: lextrapIPTrapType
lextrapIPTrapType.description: The type of SNMP over IP traps that will be sent by the adapter. Setting this variable to multiplexed(1) configures all intervention required conditions to send an irCondition trap (specific trap number 1) and for the clearing of intervention required conditions to send an irCleared trap (specific trap number 0). Setting this variable to individual(2) causes each intervention required condition to send its corresponding trap (specific traps numbered 2 through 10) and for the clearing of intervention required conditions to cause an irClearedTypeII trap (specific trap number 11). See the Trap Definitions Group for more information. Type 1 is the default for IP.

timeReset.name: timeReset
timeReset.description: A control for initiating an update of the system time and date using the specified timeSource. Setting the variable to reset will cause the system to update it's time and date using the specified time source. See timeSource.

timeSource.name: timeSource
timeSource.description: The source for setting the system time and date. If this variable is changed, the time must be reset before the change will have an effect. See timeReset.

timeUTCOffset.name: timeUTCOffset
timeUTCOffset.description: The offset in minutes from UTC (formerly GMT) of local time. Use a negative value if West of UTC. Use a positive value if East of UTC.

timeDSTEnable.name: timeDSTEnable
timeDSTEnable.description: The status of whether automatic Daylight Savings Time adjust is enabled. See timeDSTStartDate, timeDSTEndDate, and timeDSTOffset for configuration options.

timeDSTStartDate.name: timeDSTStartDate
timeDSTStartDate.description: A textual representation of the day and time the Daylight Savings Time adjust should start if enabled (see timeDSTEnable). The format of string is as follows: Byte Meaning ---- ------------------------------------------------------------ 0 Which occurence in the month of the day specified in byte 1. Valid values are: F => First Occurence 1 => First Occurence 2 => Second Occurence 3 => Third Occurence 4 => Fourth Occurence 5 => Fifth Occurence L => Last Occurence 1 A 1-digit field indicating the day of week (0=Sun..6=Sat) 2-3 A 2-digit field indicating the month. 4-5 A 2-digit field indicating the hour 6-7 A 2-digit field indicating the minute 8-9 A 2-digit field indicating the second The default setting is F004020000 which corresponds to the first Sunday of April at 2:00:00 am.

timeDSTEndDate.name: timeDSTEndDate
timeDSTEndDate.description: A textual representation of the day and time the Daylight Savings Time adjust should end if enabled (see timeDSTEnable). The format of string is as defined for timeDSTStartDate The default setting is L010020000 which corresponds to the last Sunday of October at 2:00:00 am.

timeDSTOffset.name: timeDSTOffset
timeDSTOffset.description: The offset in minutes that should be applied to local time during Daylight Savings Time.

timeServerAddress.name: timeServerAddress
timeServerAddress.description: If the specified time source is NTP (see timeSource), this is the IP address of the NTP server to use. Otherwise, the value is ignored.

timeServerName.name: timeServerName
timeServerName.description: If the specified time source is NTP (see timeSource), and the NTP server address is not set (0.0.0.0), this is the DNS domainname of the NTP server. If the specified time source is Netware (see timeSource), the is the name of Netware server. Otherwise, the value is ignored.

prtgenNumber.name: prtgenNumber
prtgenNumber.description: The number of printers, regardless of their current state, available to this adapter.

prtgenInfoTable.name: prtgenInfoTable
prtgenInfoTable.description: A table of the network adapter's attached printer information.

prtgenInfoEntry.name: prtgenInfoEntry
prtgenInfoEntry.description: An entry containing attached printer information.

prtgenPrinterIndex.name: prtgenPrinterIndex
prtgenPrinterIndex.description: A unique value used by the network adapter to identify attached printers.

prtgenPrinterName.name: prtgenPrinterName
prtgenPrinterName.description: A textual description of the make and model of the attached printer, if known.

prtgenPeripheralID.name: prtgenPeripheralID
prtgenPeripheralID.description: A textual description of the peripheral ID of the attached printer as defined by the IEEE 1284 standard, if known.

prtgenCodeRevision.name: prtgenCodeRevision
prtgenCodeRevision.description: A textual representation of the code revision level of the attached printer, if known.

prtgenResValue.name: prtgenResValue
prtgenResValue.description: This object is currently unused and reserved.

prtgenSerialNo.name: prtgenSerialNo
prtgenSerialNo.description: A textual representation of the serial number of the attached printer, if known.

prtgenStatusTable.name: prtgenStatusTable
prtgenStatusTable.description: A table of the network adapter's attached printer status.

prtgenStatusEntry.name: prtgenStatusEntry
prtgenStatusEntry.description: An entry containing attached printer status.

prtgenStatPrinterIndex.name: prtgenStatPrinterIndex
prtgenStatPrinterIndex.description: A unique value used by the network adapter to identify attached printers.

prtgenStatusIRC.name: prtgenStatusIRC
prtgenStatusIRC.description: The printer's current intervention required code.

prtgenStatusOutHopFull.name: prtgenStatusOutHopFull
prtgenStatusOutHopFull.description: The printer's current output hopper status.

prtgenStatusInputEmpty.name: prtgenStatusInputEmpty
prtgenStatusInputEmpty.description: The printer's current active input paper tray status.

prtgenStatusPaperJam.name: prtgenStatusPaperJam
prtgenStatusPaperJam.description: The printer's current paper path status.

prtgenStatusTonerError.name: prtgenStatusTonerError
prtgenStatusTonerError.description: The printer's current toner supply status.

prtgenStatusSrvcReqd.name: prtgenStatusSrvcReqd
prtgenStatusSrvcReqd.description: The printer's current service required status.

prtgenStatusDiskError.name: prtgenStatusDiskError
prtgenStatusDiskError.description: The printer's current disk sub-system status.

prtgenStatusPageComplex.name: prtgenStatusPageComplex
prtgenStatusPageComplex.description: The printer's current complex page status.

faxNumber.name: faxNumber
faxNumber.description: The number of fax modems attached to the adapter.

faxTable.name: faxTable
faxTable.description: A table of the network adapter's attached fax modems configuration data.

faxEntry.name: faxEntry
faxEntry.description: An entry containing attached fax modem configuration data.

faxIndex.name: faxIndex
faxIndex.description: A unique value used by the adapter to identify fax ports.

faxPort.name: faxPort
faxPort.description: The network adapter's port to which this modem is attached.

faxAdapterCapabilities.name: faxAdapterCapabilities
faxAdapterCapabilities.description: A bitmap representing the fax capabilities of the network adapter. Bit Value Capabilities --- ------ -------------------- 0 1 Fine Resolution 1 2 2D Encoding 2 4 T6 Encoding 3 8 ECM 4 16 Binary File Transfer 5 32 300 x 300 6 64 400 x 400 7 128 200 x 400 8 256 Uncompressed Mode 9 512 255mm Width 10 1024 303mm Width 11 2048 Legal Length 12 4096 Unlimited Length 13 8192 V.17 (14400) 14 16384 V.33 (14400) 15 32768 V.29 and V.27 (9600) 16 65536 V.29 (9600) 17 131072 V.27 (4800) 18 262144 V27 (2400)

faxModemCapabilities.name: faxModemCapabilities
faxModemCapabilities.description: A bitmap representing the fax capabilities of the attached modem. Bit Value Capabilities --- ------ -------------------- 0 1 Fine Resolution 1 2 2D Encoding 2 4 T6 Encoding 3 8 ECM 4 16 Binary File Transfer 5 32 300 x 300 6 64 400 x 400 7 128 200 x 400 8 256 Uncompressed Mode 9 512 255mm Width 10 1024 303mm Width 11 2048 Legal Length 12 4096 Unlimited Length 13 8192 V.17 (14400) 14 16384 V.33 (14400) 15 32768 V.29 and V.27 (9600) 16 65536 V.29 (9600) 17 131072 V.27 (4800) 18 262144 V27 (2400)
